<img width="305" height="296" src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/uss-cache.salvationarmy.org/10e9509e-253d-4f22-be2b-5a514d7ebf42_Majors+Ricky+and+Karla+Perez.jpg" alt="placeholder" class="img-fluid d-block my-3 mx-auto" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" loading="lazy" data-zesty-id="content:images:1:17">
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:3:7"></div>
<h5 style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:text:4:2">Majors Karla and Ricky Perez</h5>
<p class="MsoBodyText3" style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:textarea:5:91">
	<span><span lang="en-US">Majors Karla and Ricky Perez&nbsp;arrived in Hickory June of 2024.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span>
</p>
<div class="py-5" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-xl:6:12"></div>
<p class="MsoBodyText3" style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:textarea:7:70">
	Major Ricky Perez was born in Rochester, NY. He grew up in New York and Florida. He is<br>
	working on a Christian Ministry degree with Trevecca Nazarene University.<br>
	Major Karla Perez was born in Santurce, Puerto Rico. She moved to the United States when<br>
	she was 10 years old and grew up in Florida. She has a bachelor’s degree in Christian<br>
	Ministry from Trevecca Nazarene University and a master’s degree in clinical Mental Health<br>
	Counseling from Liberty University.<br>
	They got married on March 10, 2001, in Florida. They felt the call to become Officers and<br>
	entered The Salvation Army training college in 2003 and graduated in 2005. Upon&nbsp;<br>
	graduation, they were sent back home to serve in Florida. While in Florida, they served in<br>
	the following commands: Orlando, Stuart, Daytona Beach, Winter Haven, and Naples.<br>
	After 13 years of serving in the Sunshine State of Florida, they were sent out of Florida for<br>
	the first time when they were appointed to Durham, NC in 2018, where they served for 6<br>
	years.&nbsp;<br>
	They have 3 children. Ke’olani (19) attends Asbury University in Wilmore, KY. Their two<br>
	youngest sons are Josiah (16) and Ezekiel (14). Major Ricky enjoys spending time in the<br>
	outdoors, fishing, hunting, kayaking, cycling, and playing golf. Major Karla enjoys spending<br>
	time in nature, scrapbooking, crafting, and reading.<br>
	They are looking forward for all that God has in store for their time in Hickory!
</p>
